This paper proposes a new framework for Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) that focuses on producing direct energy estimates for samples. This topic is closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered by the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. Additionally, the paper applies the proposed framework to image generation tasks, which falls under the cs.CV sub-category. The paper also introduces approximation techniques to make the framework trainable, which is related to the cs.NE sub-category. Finally, the paper analyzes the properties of the induced solution, which is related to the cs.SD sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.SD, in that order.
